ImageExtractor

This program parses a webpage and downloads all of the referenced images
to a local directory.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

RUNNING

Once ImageExtractor is installed, extract-images.pl will be put into
your path, so it can easily be run.

    extract-images.pl --help # for more information

DEPENDENCIES

The Makefile.PL knows about the dependencies, but just in case, here
they are again (assuming you have a modern perl, such as 5.12):

    * HTML::TreeBuilder::XPath
    * LWP::UserAgent
    * Moose
    * Pod::Usage
    * Try::Tiny
    * URI::URL

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc extract-images.pl

